OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1778220037
OL,3,CCalocane charge 'more understandable
OL,4,Cas second degree murder', inquiry hears
OL,6,FIt would have been "more
OL,7,Funderstandable" for Valdo Calocane to
OL,8,Fhave been charged with second-degree
OL,9,Fmurder instead of manslaughter, an
OL,10,Finquiry has heard.
OL,12,FParanoid schizophrenic Valdo Calocane
OL,13,Fstabbed three people and tried to kill
OL,14,Fthree others with a stolen van in
OL,15,FNottingham city centre in June 2023.
OL,16,FHe was charged with manslaughter.
OL,26,@nD@TOUoD@OO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1778220037
OL,3,CCalocane charge 'more understandable
OL,4,Cas second degree murder', inquiry hears
OL,6,FBut Anthony Rogers, the chief
OL,7,Finspector at His Majesty's Crown
OL,8,FProsecution Service Inspectorate
OL,9,F(HMCPSI), told the Nottingham Attacks
OL,10,FInquiry on Wednesday that manslaughter
OL,11,Fwas "a very difficult legal concept
OL,12,Ffor ordinary people outside of the
OL,13,Fsystem to understand".
OL,15,F"It would have possibly been more
OL,16,Funderstandable and a little bit more `
OL,17,F'acceptable' is the wrong word, but it
OL,18,Fis the word I am going to use ` if it
OL,19,Fhad been second degree murder, not
OL,20,Fmanslaughter," he said.
OL,26,@sD@EOUuD@UO]wD@AOU|D@NO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1778220037
OL,3,CCalocane charge 'more understandable
OL,4,Cas second degree murder', inquiry hears
OL,6,F"It's very difficult, I think, for
OL,7,Fanybody to accept in the circumstances
OL,8,Fof this case that their loved ones
OL,9,Fhave been killed by someone and it's a
OL,10,Fmanslaughter.
OL,12,F"You know, that word 'murder' is
OL,13,Fsomething that's very important to
OL,14,Fpeople."
OL,16,FA report in March 2024 found the Crown
OL,17,FProsecution Service's decision to
OL,18,Faccept triple killer Valdo Calocane's
OL,19,Fguilty pleas to manslaughter was
OL,20,Fcorrect.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUvD@HO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1778220037
OL,3,CCalocane charge 'more understandable
OL,4,Cas second degree murder', inquiry hears
OL,6,FIt added prosecutors "could not have
OL,7,Fproceeded on the murder allegations
OL,8,Fbecause of the clear and unambiguous
OL,9,Ffindings of the prosecution and
OL,10,Fdefence psychiatric reports that the
OL,11,Foffender's actions were because of
OL,12,Fpure psychosis".
OL,14,FBut the report also pointed to a
OL,15,Frecommendation made in the 2006 Law
OL,16,FCommission report that the current two-
OL,17,Ftier structure of homicide law `
OL,18,Fnamely murder and manslaughter `
OL,19,Fshould be changed to a three-tier
OL,20,Fstructure that includes second degree
OL,21,Fmurder, the inquiry was told.
OL,26,@nD@VOUtD@OO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1778220038
OL,3,CCalocane charge 'more understandable
OL,4,Cas second degree murder', inquiry hears
OL,6,FWhen asked by Julian Blake KC, counsel
OL,7,Ffor the inquiry, if the HMCPSI
OL,8,F"considers that the law should
OL,9,Fchange", Mr Rogers replied: "It's not
OL,10,Fa matter for HMCPSI, it's a matter for
OL,11,FParliament whether they adopt this."
OL,13,FCalocane fatally stabbed
OL,14,Fundergraduates Barnaby Webber and
OL,15,FGrace O'Malley-Kumar, both 19, on
OL,16,FIlkeston Road, Nottingham, in the
OL,17,Fearly hours of June 13 2023.
OL,26,@pD@AOUqD@GO]qD@]OUsD@dO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1778220038
OL,3,CCalocane charge 'more understandable
OL,4,Cas second degree murder', inquiry hears
OL,6,FHe went on to kill grandfather Ian
OL,7,FCoates, 65, in the Mapperley Park area
OL,8,Faround an hour later, stealing his van
OL,9,Fand using it to run over pedestrians
OL,10,Fat two locations in Nottingham city
OL,11,Fcentre.
OL,13,FHe later admitted manslaughter and
OL,14,Fattempted murder, and was sentenced to
OL,15,Fan indefinite hospital order in
OL,16,FJanuary 2024 after prosecutors
OL,17,Faccepted his not guilty pleas to
OL,18,Fmurder on the grounds of diminished
OL,19,Fresponsibility.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1778220038
OL,3,CCalocane charge 'more understandable
OL,4,Cas second degree murder', inquiry hears
OL,6,FThe decision was widely criticised by
OL,7,Fbereaved families, who called
OL,8,Fdiminished responsibility laws
OL,9,F"archaic" and insisted that they
OL,10,Fbelieved Calocane was a murderer.
OL,12,FThis is despite the Court of Appeal
OL,13,Frefusing to change Calocane's sentence
OL,14,Fin May 2024.
OL,26,@qD@AOUqD@IO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
